	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=180599><span id= >Treesong</span></a><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.81]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You can get lucky on this drop. I came to the Ghoul Lords room and killed its PH. Next popped the Ghoul Lord, no scalp, just a Skull Shaped Barbute. Then a PH again, and then the Lord again which now dropped both a Barbute and the Scalp!<br><br>Unfortunately the scalp does not much for me yet, I am almost max KOS to the frogs, being a Cazic Thule Troll that has hunted Guk in his youthfull days. However, I think when I can get my faction to Indifferent by killing a million frogs (I think thats the highest us Evil Cazic worshippers can get when it comes to bare faction)this scalp will lift me up a good deal since going from Indiff to Warmly is a much shorter stretch then the dreaded &quot;scowling&quot; and &quot;dubious&quot; stretches. Not sure if it will take me all the way&nbsp;&nbsp;to warmly though.<br><br>Wolfform (tested on outside froggies that guard the entrance) did not un-KOS me either, but it did take my druid from Dubious to INdiff.  So I am still unsure where Wolfform comes into the whole equation for evil races. <br><br>I guess the first thing I have to do is max my faction by killing (Your faction could not possibly get any higher.) and then see what all the illusions and the scalp do.<br><br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jul 21 06:41:55 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
