	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=204115><span id= >Naitraen the Sly</span></a><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.88]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Thank you, Troodon, thank you!&nbsp;&nbsp;Thank you for trying to spreak a little sanity/brain power into this dim-bulb world! For anyone's information, items that have a &quot;faction modifier&quot; only modify one faction -- the faction found in that zone (or, <u>a</u> faction, if, like Lower Guk, there is more than one faction for all of the inhabitants).  The <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16350 target=akztarg>Planar Traveler's Manual</a>, or <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=7106 target=akztarg>Amulet of the Haven</a> do NOT give you better faction with the Inhabitants of the Plane of Hate.  They give you better faction with the inhabitants of the zone in which they are earned.  The same with the Scalp.  The only differences being, that 1) it is looted instead of earned, and 2) it modifies the other faction than the one from whom it's looted.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Dec 16 17:05:40 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>[IKS BST] Naiphands Clawsof'Rile<br>{HEF BRD] Naitclub Torchsinger <br>[ERU(!) SHD(?!)] Naitraen Lukeimyurdad<br>Tarew Marr &lt;Well of Souls&gt;<br>"It's always darkest,<br>just after the lights go out..."</td></tr>
